<h2 style="color:black; font-size: 120%; font-weight: bold; text-align: center;" id="june2020">June2020</h2>

<iframe width="100%" height="1250" src="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1LqgM6Bv2DC2UVbdPMaUVlNOLNo_1f_3WZ5FWqHEc8L4/edit?usp=sharing"></iframe>

<h2 style="color:black; font-size: 120%; font-weight: bold; text-align: center;" id="faq">FAQ</h2>

<ul style="color:black; font-size: 100%; font-weight: bold; text-align: left;">
  <li>When can I start to go to my office?</li>
</ul>

<p>Every Monday starting June 8 2020. Exception for experimental folks, IT staff and Admin staff.
<ins>You are, however, highly encouraged to work from home as much as possible.</ins></p>

<ul style="color:black; font-size: 100%; font-weight: bold; text-align: left;">
  <li>Can I go to my office or is there a new office allocated for me?</li>
</ul>

<p>Please check the <a href="#offices">table</a> above. If you have a new office please be mindful 
of the privacy of the person hosting you. Also please maintain proper hygiene in the 
office by cleaning door handles etc.</p>

<ul style="color:black; font-size: 100%; font-weight: bold; text-align: left;">
  <li>What will ENS provide in terms of personal protection?</li>
</ul>

<p>The first time you visit each person should get a â€˜kitâ€™ containing washable masks and 
handgels.</p>

<ul style="color:black; font-size: 100%; font-weight: bold; text-align: left;">
  <li>What is the protocol to wear masks at ENS?</li>
</ul>

<p>You need to wear masks at all times except when you are alone in your office.</p>

<ul style="color:black; font-size: 100%; font-weight: bold; text-align: left;">
  <li>Can I plan to go every Monday then?</li>
</ul>

<p>In principle, it might be possible. However we need to maintain a maximum of 20 folks at
any given time in the lab. The priority being given to experimental folks, IT and administrative staff. 
For the time being please fill out the <a href="#june2020">table</a> above and the lab direction will decide and inform.
Please check back this website again.</p>

<ul style="color:black; font-size: 100%; font-weight: bold; text-align: left;">
  <li>But I really need to recover stuff from my office, print etc. before June 8</li>
</ul>

<p>In this case, email Alexandre Schubnel (aschubnel@geologie.ens.fr) or 
Laurent Bopp (bopp@lmd.ens.fr) asking for an exception. They will try to fit you in.</p>

<ul style="color:black; font-size: 100%; font-weight: bold; text-align: left;">
  <li>What is recommened in terms of getting to the lab?</li>
</ul>

<p>It is highly recommened that you try to avoid public transportation at all. 
If you do not have a choice then try to take them during non-rush hours.</p>

<ul style="color:black; font-size: 100%; font-weight: bold; text-align: left;">
  <li>What are the rush hours and what do I need to do in this case?</li>
</ul>

<p>Officially its between 6:30-9:30 and 16:00-19:00. In this case you need to fill out this <a href="https://we.tl/t-pEkPOSUEqz">form</a>
and have it signed either by Alex or Laurent.</p>

<ul style="color:black; font-size: 100%; font-weight: bold; text-align: left;">
  <li>What are the modalities of entering and exiting ENS?</li>
</ul>

<p>You need to enter the building through 24 rue Lhomond and exit through 8 rue Erasme.</p>

<ul style="color:black; font-size: 100%; font-weight: bold; text-align: left;">
  <li>What are the official hours to work at ENS?</li>
</ul>

<p>Monday through Friday 7am through 9pm. ENS is closed on weekends and holidays.</p>

<ul style="color:black; font-size: 100%; font-weight: bold; text-align: left;">
  <li>For any other questions/concerns/worries please email me and Iâ€™ll do my best to sort it.</li>
</ul>

